				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is getting the Scepter Frame in Akheva Ruins bard-soloable?<a name="30524"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 25 04 11:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Honestly?  
<br />

<br />
It is extremely difficult since alot of the mobs Harm Touch.  As a cleric, I solo'd that piece (it is only a turn in after all).  Getting to the room for the turn in was the most difficult part (died 4 times enroute).
<br />

<br />
Once at the room, there are a few mobs near the doorway to lull/paci (died 2 times here). 
<br />

<br />
Go in and to the left, where you'll likely agro a couple of mobs (2?) (died 3 times here).  Kill them off FAST (extremely fast respawns in this room), and med up as best you can.  
<br />

<br />
Once you've killed/med, lull your way onto the &quot;stage&quot; towards the back-center of the room.  You *WILL* need to lull/charm-kill the mobs from up on top.  (Allowing them to run WILL get you killed super quickly). (died 5 times here)
<br />

<br />
Kill off the sacrificial remains until the turn in mob pop's (technically, 5 turn in mobs can pop at the same time), do the turn in, and get the heck out of dodge.
<br />

<br />
Some of you are sitting there thinking... If a Cleric can do it, a bard can do it without a problem.  One point to remember, a Cleric can have FT15, C5, SP, MC3, pot9.  THAT is alot of mana regen, and I used EVERY bit of it.
<br />

<br />
As you can see, from all my deaths, it was a personal goal to acheive.</span></td>
