			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is getting the Scepter Frame in Akheva Ruins bard-soloable?<a name="31294"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 29 04 8:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Done this with my shaman, but the same method should work fine (or even better) for a bard!
<br />

<br />
<b>Shaman Method</b>
<br />
Sow outside, throw on all hp buffs, zone in, quiessence (heal over time), invis, run as far as you can to the room taking good care that you trigger all the traps, run back out and zone. Traps are now disarmed for a while.
<br />

<br />
Wait a moment for train to go, zone back, shrink twice and invis again. Run invis all the way to the sacrificial pit, but run up the stairs around the back and then drop down (still invis). If you stick near the sides at all times mobs shouldn't aggro, but con them just to be sure they don't see invis. A small number of mobs do see through invis but with care you can avoid them.
<br />

<br />
At this point with your back to the wall and shrunk twice, you can remove invis, kill the 3 closest mobs and repeat until the trigger mob spawns.
<br />

<br />
<b>Bard adaptations</b>
<br />
As bards can't shrink, either use some shrink potions or gnome illusion if you have it. Its important to be teeny tiny sized so as not to aggro any mobs when you drop invis with your back to the wall.
<br />

<br />
On the plus side, bards with FM can probably skip the whole malarky with setting off traps and training them to the zone - just use invis to get as far in as you can, if you do get aggro, fade it off once you reach the main room with sacrificial pit, and then move invis up the back to drop down by the remains without ever aggroing the 4-arms.
<br />

<br />
The key to the whole thing is the use of invis and shrink, don't try to lull or fight your way in solo.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=606506">Goldolin</a><br>
Bard of 63 concerts</span></td>
